The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: Japanese auto maker Nissan Motor Co today unveiled the initial design of its new global small car that will be produced in five countries, including India, China and Thailand. Production of the car will start in May 2010 at a new factory in Chennai. The factory is being built by Nissan and Renault S.A. The car will be sold in more than 150 countries.                             
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: Network equipment manufacturer Cisco Systems will buy Norway-based Tandberg ASA for 17.2 billion kroner (approximately $3 billion). Cisco will pay 153.50 kroner a share in cash. The price is 11 per cent higher than Tandbergs closing price in Oslo trading yesterday.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 1: The Supreme Court today refused to halt Bombay High Courts decision that allowed Mukesh Ambani-led RIL to amend its plea on a gas supply deal with NTPC at a committed price citing government policy.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 1: GE chairman Jeffery Immelt today met Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and apprised him of the companys plans for the country. Immelt is slated to hold a joint press conference with Wipro chairman Azim Premji on Friday.                                                                                                                           
